Book Marguerite Kondracke for a Speaking Engagement
Businesses, Non-profit organizations, event planners and companies across the country have worked closely with our booking agents to hire Marguerite Kondracke for a speaking engagements, guest appearances, product endorsements and corporate events. Many of those same clients have continued to turn to our speakers bureau as we can easily align Marguerite Kondracke’s availability with their upcoming seminar, gala, annual conference, corporate function, and grand opening. Our close relationship with Marguerite Kondracke’s  booking agent and management team further enables us to provide inquiring clients with Marguerite Kondracke’s speaking fee and appearance cost.
If your goal is to hire Marguerite Kondracke to be your next keynote speaker or to be the next brand ambassador our celebrity speakers bureau can assist. If Marguerite Kondracke’s booking fee is outside your companies budget or your unable to align with his appearance availability, our booking agents can provide you a list of talent that aligns with your event theme, budget and event date.
					

Since 2004, Marguerite W. Kondracke has been President and CEO of America's Promise Alliance, founded in 1997 by General Colin Powell. With more than 300 national partners, America's Promise is currently focused on addressing the nation's high school dropout crisis. During her 40-year career, Marguerite has been both an entrepreneur and a public servant. She brings to America's Promise Alliance extensive multi-sector experience as an advocate for children and families. Before joining the Alliance, Marguerite served as Special Assistant to U.S. Senator Lamar Alexander and Staff Director for the Senate Subcommittee on Children and Families. Previously, she also co-founded and was CEO of the nation's largest employersponsored child care company, Bright Horizons Family Solutions, one of Fortune's "100 Best Companies to Work For." Recently, Marguerite was named one of the "Top 50 People of Power and Influence in 2008" by The Non-Profit Times. She is a board member of the Independent Sector and also a trustee of Duke University. Marguerite is married to award-winning journalist Morton Kondracke, and they have four children and two grandchildren.



