Background

		Mrs. Marguerite W. Kondracke, also known as Salle, serves as the Chief Executive Officer and President at America’s Promise Alliance. Mrs. Kondracke served as President and Chief Executive Officer of CorporateFamily Solutions Inc. from February 1987 to July 1998. She co-founded corporate family Solutions Inc. in 1987. She serves at LoyaltyPoint, Inc. She served as President and Chief Executive Officer of The Brown Schools from September 2001 to March 2003. Mrs. Kondracke ... served as the Chairman of the Board and Chief Executive Officer of Frontline Group, Inc. from July 1999 to August 2001. She served as Chief Executive Officer of Bright Horizons Family Solutions from July 1998 to January 1999. She was a Co-founder of Bright Horizons Family Solutions. She served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of America's Promise - The Alliance for Youth. Mrs. Kondracke served as the Chairman of Ladies Professional Golf Association. She served as Co-Chairman of the Board of Bright Horizons Family Solutions Inc. from May 1999 to December 2001. She served as the Chairman of the Nashville Area Chamber of Commerce. She serves as a Director of Malaria No More and of GSV Advisors. She serves as a Board Member of Rosetta Stone (UK) Limited. Mrs. Kondracke serves as Board Member and Secretary of Independent Sector. She has been a Director of Saks Incorporated since 1996. She has been a Director of Corporation for National and Community Service since March 29, 2012. Mrs. Kondracke has been an Independent Director of Bright Horizons Family Solutions, Inc. since December 2, 2004. She serves as a Director of Ladies Professional Golf Association. She serves as a Director of Proffitt's Inc., MagneTek Inc. and Phoenix Healthcare Corporation. She served as a Member of the Advisory Board at Avondale Partners, LLC. She served as a Director of Teachscape, Inc. Mrs. Kondracke served on Bright Horizons Family Solutions Inc.'s Board of Directors from 1998 to March 2003. She served as a Director of Rosetta Stone, Inc. from December 1, 2011 to January 19, 2016. She served as a Director of CorporateFamily Solutions Inc., since February 1987. She is a delegate to the Presidential Summit for Children. During her 40-year career, Mrs. Kondracke has been both an entrepreneur and a public servant, focusing on the needs of children and families. She served as Special Assistant to U.S. Senator Lamar Alexander and Staff Director of Senate Subcommittee on Children and Families from April 2003 to September 2004. Mrs. Kondracke served as Commissioner of Human Services in former Governor Lamar Alexander's cabinet. She serves as also a Member of the Board of Directors of Saks Fifth Avenue. She has been an Independent Director of LifePoint Health, inc. (formerly known as LifePoint Hospitals, Inc.) since November 2007. She serves as a Trustee of Washington's Arena Stage. She has been a Director of The American Academy, LLC since May 2013. She serves as a Board of Trustees Duke University Medical Center. She served as Special Assistant to U.S. Senator Lamar Alexander. Throughout her career, Mrs. Kondracke has received numerous awards and honors; including being named a Purpose Prize Fellow, awarded by Civic Ventures to those over 60 taking on society’s biggest challenges. Ms. Sallee served in Tennessee state government where she developed and led a statewide four-year “Healthy Children Initiative.“ She was named by The Non-Profit Times as one of the “Top 50 People of Power and Influence in 2008.” She is an alumna and a trustee of Duke University, where she co-chairs Duke Engage. Mrs. Kondracke received a Bachelor of Arts from Duke University and a Master's Degree in Psychology from Austin Peay University.Read Full Background




